									<br>
									In this event, a total of 63 CSE first year students participated. The “<b>Come for Code</b>” event contained an interactive tutorial for the development of Android Apps in a Google Chrome extension called “<b>MIT App Inventor</b>”. This extension is an interactive Drag & Drop application to make apps which can be used to make simple android apps and show the different programming paradigms to the fresh minds of students. Students were also introduced to ACM Student Chapter and its machinery. Students showed high enthusiasm for the event.
