								<h3>Press Release for Publication</h3>
								<p>Department of Computer Sc. & Engineering, Chandigarh College of Engineering & Technology (Degree

									Wing), Sector -26, Chandigarh is started ACM@CCET Student chapter and organized one day seminar on 

									Cloud Computing  & Big Data  Analytics on 6th Nov 2015 at CCET (Degree Wing) campus, Sector -26, 

									Chandigarh.<br>

									The newly created ACM@CCET Student chapter was officially inaugurated by chief guest Dr. Mukesh 

									Mohania , Global Chief Architect, IBM Research, India & Treasurer of ACM India,  Prof.( Dr.) M. S. 

									Gujral, Principal, CCET(Deg. Wing.) Chandigarh and Dr Sunil K Singh, Professor  & HOD , CSE 

									Deptt. <br>

									Dr. Mukesh Mohania gave a wonderful, interactive and motivation-cum-informative seminar on Big 

									Data and Cloud Computing by teaching the roots of their existence and their scope in coming time. A 

									10-20 mins Q/A session was held after the session. After the lunch break, Dr. Mukesh, Dr. Sunil and all 

									the ACM@CCET members had around the table discussion on various opportunities for the CSE 

									students to learn scientific and practical approach of computer science under ACM students chapter.<br>

									In the inauguration ceremony, Prof.( Dr.) M. S. Gujral, pleased and acknowledge the effort of CSE 

									department to most awaited Programming and Computing student chapter in connection with ACM ( 

									Association of Computing machinery) at CCET, Chandigarh. Dr Gujral highlighted the various benefits 

									of ACM and told ACM provides unique outlook on how current and emerging technologies are being 

									useful in day to day life. ACM has evolved as an interactive intellectual association of likewise mind 

									bridging the gap between academics and practitioners of the art of Computer Science. The aim of ACM 

									can only be achieved by taking lead role in computing by computer science student of CCET to transfer 

									their knowledge into implementation based expertise. He thanks Dr Mukesh Mohania for inauguration 

									of ACM student chapter and giving seminar on Cloud Computing & Big Data  Analytics to the CCET 

									students.<br>

									Dr Sunil Kr Singh HOD CSE highlighted the ACM student chapter objective in his speech and told that 

									the Association for Computing Machinery (ACM) is an international learned society for computing and 

									It was founded in 1947. Dr Singh told that ACM provides a platform to sustain close academic and 

									research alliance between higher education institutions and research organization from globe to facilitate 

									the innovation, collaboration and knowledge for achieving excellence in all academics activities. The 

									study of computation is paramount to the discipline of computer science and ACM itself is solely 

									dedicated to COMPUTING. 
<br>
									Dr Singh expects that this initiation will prove to be highly beneficial for the students in overall 

									academic growth. Through this student chapter, they will have an opportunity to interact with the 

									experts of Computer Science Industry from all over the world.  It will provide them a means to portray 

									their talent and innovation to the world. He thanked to Dr Mukesh Mohania for helping to start this 

									student chapter in alliance with ACM and request to provide similar learning opportunity to CCET 

									students in future also.
<br>
